    <title>Portfolio - Design</title>
</head>

<body style="background-color: rgb(111, 134, 132);">
    <div>
        <%- include ('partials/navbar.ejs') %>
        <br><br>
        <hr style="border: none; border-top: 2px solid; color: rgb(54, 65, 64); width: 30%; margin: 20px auto;">
        <h1 style="font-family: fleur; font-weight: bolder; text-align: center; color: rgb(219, 208, 164); font-size: 80px;">Portfolio - Design</h1>
        <br>
    </div>

    <div class="container" class="column">
        
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div id="carousel1" class="carousel slide carousel-smaller">
                    <div class="carousel-inner">
                        <div class="carousel-item active">
                            <img src="/images/webpage_home.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="homepage">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/webpage_about.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="aboutpage">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/webpage_portfolio.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="portfoliopage">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/webpage_contact.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="contactpage">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/moodboard.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="moodboard">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#carousel1" data-bs-slide="prev">
                        <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
                    </button>
                    <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#carousel1" data-bs-slide="next">
                        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-center">
                <div class="row">
                    <h4 style="font-family: filosofia, serif; color: rgb(219, 208, 164);">Portfolio Web Page Design</h4>
                    <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordion1" style="color: rgb(54, 65, 64); font-family: filosofia, serif; font-weight: 400;">
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion1-collapseOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion1-collapseOne">
                                    Tool(s) used
                                </button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="accordion1-collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion1">
                                <div class="accordion-body">Adobe Illustrator</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion1-collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion1-collapseTwo">
                                Timeline
                              </button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="accordion1-collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion1">
                              <div class="accordion-body">About 2 to 2 and a half weeks</div>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="accordion-item">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion1-collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion1-collapseThree">
                                Design principles
                              </button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="accordion1-collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion1">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                <p>Slide 5 is the moodboard I used to inspire my whole portfolio web design.</p>
                                For this project, I was not focusing on the design by itself but rather trying to implemet the design principles that I have learnt. 
                                For the first page of my website, I used the design principle of symmetry(balance). When we split the page into two, 
                                we can see that half of the page is filled with a description while the other half if filled with graphics. The graphic is a tracing of 
                                myself and butterflies which are one of my favourite things. This would make the website feels more “me” and original. 
                                For the second page is used the design principle of vertical rhythm. I used cards to organise the elements and put them in a vertical manner. 
                                For the third page, I used the design principle of emphasis as the main information is the biggest size and in the middle of the page. 
                                Lastly for the last page, I used the design principle of vertical rhythm. All the information are organised and aligned vertically in boxes to 
                                show a hierarchy on which is the preferred way of communication. 

                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="accordion-item">
                              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion1-collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion1-collapseFour">
                                  Key takeaways
                                </button>
                              </h2>
                              <div id="accordion1-collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion1">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                  From this project, I gained a deeper understanding of the importance of consistency in web design. 
                                    Consistency simplifies user interactions by providing a predictable and intuitive experience, enabling users to 
                                    navigate and absorb content with ease. By maintaining uniformity in elements like layout, color scheme, typography, 
                                    and interactive components, I reduced the cognitive load on users, helping them quickly familiarize themselves with 
                                    the page and interact with confidence. This project reinforced that consistency is not just a design preference but a 
                                    crucial principle that enhances usability and promotes a seamless, cohesive experience for visitors.
                                </div>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        </div>

        <br><br>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div id="carousel2" class="carousel slide carousel-smaller">
                    <div class="carousel-inner">
                        <div class="carousel-item active">
                            <img src="/images/namecard_front.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="front">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/namecard_back.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="back">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
                            <img src="/images/moodboard.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="moodboard">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#carousel2" data-bs-slide="prev">
                        <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
                    </button>
                    <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#carousel2" data-bs-slide="next">
                        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-center">
                <div class="row">
                    <h4 style="font-family: filosofia, serif; color: rgb(219, 208, 164);">Business Card Design</h4>
                    <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordion2" style="color: rgb(54, 65, 64); font-family: filosofia, serif; font-weight: 400;">
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                          <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion2-collapseOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2-collapseOne">
                              Tool(s) used
                            </button>
                          </h2>
                          <div id="accordion2-collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion2">
                            <div class="accordion-body">Adobe Illustrator</div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                          <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion2-collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2-collapseTwo">
                              Timeline
                            </button>
                          </h2>
                          <div id="accordion2-collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion2">
                            <div class="accordion-body">About 2 to 2 and a half weeks</div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                          <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion2-collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2-collapseThree">
                              Design principles
                            </button>
                          </h2>
                          <div id="accordion2-collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion2">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                              <p>On the 3rd slide is the same moodboard i used as my portfolio web page design. It was the same project and I was to showcase how my business card and porfolio are related.</p>
                                    The design principle I used for the front is emphasis as the font used is the darkest among the other elements. 
                                    As for the front of the card, I used both “Coquette” and “Sinete” as the font to make use of contrast as one of the fonts is sans and 
                                    the other is serif.  Again, the butterfly is there which serves as a meaning behind it and as something for people to remember my company, 
                                    which is a therapy company, by. For the back of the card, it has my name specifically on it and in a smaller font below my name, there is a word 
                                    “therapist” which represents my role in that company. This creates a visual hierarchy to tell readers my name and then my job title. The design 
                                    principle used at the back of the card is also emphasis since there is a space separating my name together with my job title and the contact 
                                    information. My personal contact details are being put on the top right and then the company's address, website and social media is listed next.
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                          <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#accordion2-collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2-collapseFour">
                              Key takeaways
                            </button>
                          </h2>
                          <div id="accordion2-collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion2">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                              A key takeaway from designing this name card is the value of simplicity and effective hierarchy. Simplicity in design makes essential 
                              information easy to locate and remember, ensuring that the card serves its purpose efficiently. Establishing a clear font hierarchy further reinforces 
                              this clarity; larger, prominently placed text signifies primary information, while smaller text denotes secondary details. Thoughtful font sizing and 
                              placement work together to create a natural flow, making the card not only visually appealing but also intuitive for quick reference. This approach enhances 
                              both the functionality and memorability of the design.
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    <style>
